-- ── Calendar Icons Generator ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Calendar Icons Generator is a free, browser-based web tool that creates a full year's worth of custom, dated calendar-style icons in a single click, designed primarily for people who want personalized daily folder or app icons in tools like Notion, Windows folders, and mobile home screens. Built with Next.js by an independent developer, the tool grew out of the creator's own use of Notion for journaling and project tracking, where distinct, date-specific icons make it easier to visually navigate daily pages at a glance. Users design one icon template, choosing background, header, outline, and font colors, selecting a date format (such as 1, 01, or 1st) and a day-label style (full name, abbreviation, or single initial), and adjusting font style and size, with a live preview showing how the icon looks across a full month before committing. Selecting a target year and clicking generate produces a downloadable zip file containing 365 (or 366 in a leap year) individually dated icon images, ready to drop into a Notion icon library, a folder-naming workflow, or any other system that supports custom per-item icons. Because the tool is explicitly free with no account, subscription, or payment required, it functions more as a niche utility and portfolio project than a commercial SaaS product, and it should be evaluated on convenience and customization depth rather than pricing or support tiers.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Free web tool; no account, subscription, or payment required$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(NULL, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Not publicly disclosed (independent developer project)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Not publicly disclosed$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Calendar Icons Generator: Free Tool for Custom Dated Calendar Icons$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Calendar Icons Generator is a free web tool that creates 365 custom, dated calendar icons for Notion, folders, and mobile devices in one click. See how it works.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Calendar Icons Generator is a small, free, browser-based utility that solves a specific and fairly niche design problem: generating a complete year's worth of individually dated calendar-style icons from a single design template. Rather than manually creating 365 separate icon images to represent each day of the year, a user designs one icon once, and the tool automatically produces the full set with the correct day-of-week label and date stamped onto each image. The tool is built using Next.js and was created by an individual developer rather than a company or design agency; according to the creator, the idea emerged from personal use of Notion for daily journaling and project management, where giving each daily page a distinct, date-labeled icon makes it noticeably easier to visually scan and navigate a long list of dated entries compared with using the same generic icon repeated hundreds of times. The design workflow is built around a live preview: users adjust the background color, header color, outline color, and font colors, choose how the date itself should be displayed (as a bare number like 1, a zero-padded number like 01, or an ordinal like 1st), and choose how the day-of-week label appears, whether as a full name such as Monday, a short abbreviation such as Mon, or a single initial such as M. Font style and size can be adjusted for both the header and date text, including the option to use any font already installed on the user's own system by typing in its name, and a dark mode is available in the design interface itself for users working in low-light conditions. Once a design is finalized, the user selects which calendar year they want icons generated for and clicks a single generate button, which produces a downloadable zip archive containing an individual icon image for every day of that year, correctly labeled with its date and day of the week. The tool explicitly markets this as a one-click, entirely free process, with no account creation, payment, or subscription required at any point, positioning it closer to a free utility or indie side project than a commercial SaaS product. The generated icons are intended primarily for three common use cases that the tool's own site calls out: customizing daily pages inside Notion (a popular use case given the tool's origin story), renaming and re-icon-ing folders on Windows to visually distinguish dated folders, and setting custom icons for date-specific items on iOS or Android mobile devices. Because Calendar Icons Generator is free, has no growth-stage funding, company structure, or public pricing history to research, and is maintained by a single developer rather than a team, it is best understood and evaluated in this directory as a lightweight, purpose-built utility rather than as an enterprise or venture-backed software product; its value proposition rests entirely on how much time it saves compared with manually creating or sourcing 365 individually dated icon graphics.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'a45a42d6-f099-41c6-ae25-4e9fbe792489';

